    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis is a regression of https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/issues/3304 when this code was moved to nvim core such that it uses a new caching mechanism.\n\nWhen you edit a query buffer, it needs to clear all the queries in the system on save.\n\nBONUS CONTEXT: nvim-treesitter actually adds some **legacy** misdirection here in its **legacy** version by having **a legacy autocmd that actually does nothing**: https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/issues/3304#issuecomment-3114942889.\n\nA correct version of this needs to be added to neovim core.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nrc file:\n```lua\n-- Run this file as `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\nfor name, url in pairs {\n  'https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n} do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\nend\n\nvim.opt.cursorline = true\n\nrequire(\"nvim-treesitter.configs\").setup({\n    highlight = { enable = true },\n    ensure_installed = {'lua'},\n})\n```\n\nOpen minimal.lua.\n\nEdit the lua highlights query `nvim_issue/1/queries/lua/highlights.scm` to add a new `meow` capture or delete the entire file contents, either way, whatever.\n\nObserve the following doesn't reflect the changes:\n\n```\n:lua vim.print(vim.treesitter.query.get('lua', 'highlights').captures)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe query state should have its cache invalidated like nvim-treesitter used to do correctly before the functionality was moved into nvim core.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2 3.5.14\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnixpkgs",
